commit.message: Explicitly use python2 in shebang lines
Removed commented out variable in debian rules
Pass command line arguments from build_inplace to setup.py
Refactored setup.py to be PEP-8 compliant
Install README in the docs for the debian package
Use pybuild for the debian build system
Increased debian compatibility level to 11 and updated dependencies

Fix encoding of UTF-16 surrogate pairs


UCS4 escape sequences aren't valid JSON, so when Py_UNICODE_WIDE
is defined, UTF-16 surrogate pairs need to be produced.

Decoding retains the surrogate pairs as separate code points
instead of joining them, something that perhaps should be
improved, but isn't invalid (just inconvenient)
Updated copyright years and stripped licensing info from source code
Removed no longer used pycompat file
Build depend on python >= 2.7 as older versions are not in debian anymore
Implemented recursion limit check for encoding/decoding arrays and objects
